# PackTrac Architecture Rules

## Routes

- Every route must be associated with a view component.
- Use lazy loading for dashboard-area routes: `component: () => import('../views/XView.vue')`.
- Route names must be kebab-case and match the view name conceptually.

## Views

- Every view must be a Single File Component (SFC) in `src/views/`.
- Naming: `*View.vue` (e.g. `PackagesView.vue`).
- Views are presentational; business logic goes in services, stores, or viewmodels.

## Services

- Services live in `src/services/`.
- One service per domain entity (packageService, warehouseService, etc.).
- Data source: per project phase (Entregable 1: LocalStorage only).
- All service methods must define parameter and return types.

## Components

- Shared components in `src/components/`.
- Reusable components (table, chart, selector) must be generic and configurable.
- Use props for configuration; emit events for user actions.

## Environment Variables

- All env variables must be defined in `.env` (and `.env.example` for docs).
- Use `import.meta.env.VITE_*` for Vite env vars.
- Never commit `.env`; it is in `.gitignore`.

## Models

- Domain types in `src/models/`.
- All classes from the class diagram must be implemented as TypeScript interfaces/types.
